Tell about work board.

A workboard is a visual tool used to track and manage work items, tasks, or projects. It's often used in agile project management, Kanban, and other workflow systems. A typical workboard consists of columns or lanes that represent different stages of work, such as "To-Do", "In Progress", and "Done". Team members or individuals can move items across these columns to reflect the current status of their tasks or projects.
